# Architecture Standards

Architecture drives implementation — not the reverse.

## Default Hakimo shape (Next apps)

```
app/          → thin routes only
modules|features/<domain>/
  actions/    → "use server" auth + orchestration + revalidate
  services/   → business rules
  components/ → UI
lib/repositories/ → DB access
```

Adapt to the repo's existing names (`modules` vs `features` vs DDD layers) — never invent a parallel structure.

## Boundaries

- UI does not embed SQL/business rules
- Actions do not become god-files of queries
- Repositories map DB ↔ domain; services own rules + audit
- Shared UI lives in design-system / `components/ui` / SweetFlow — domain UI stays in the module
- Cross-page logic is never owned by a single `page.tsx` — see `REUSE.mdc` (single implementation, correct ownership)

## Change control

Ask before changing folder architecture, auth model, or multi-tenant boundaries.

## Multi-surface products

Separate shells when needed: admin, operational (POS/field), auth, public (QR/menu). Do not force one layout on all.
